<html>
0.23 (05/16/2015)
<ol>
<li>Added libspoton_delete_urls() to libspoton. Version updated to 0.10.</li>
<li>Allow adjustment of the iteration count in the file encryption tool.</li>
<li>Allow configuration of alternating row colors of Chat, E-Mail, and URLs participants. Please see Options.</li>
<li>Allow configuration of the kernel's cache purge timer.</li>
<li>Allow importing of URLs without Import Credentials. Only plaintext URLs will be imported.</li>
<li>Assume zero pointer defaults in Qt::value().</li>
<li>Close progress dialogs instead of hiding them. Please see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shroedinger%27s_Cat.</li>
<li>Compute automatic digests in threads. Safely interrupt on process termination. Completed futures are occasionally removed.</li>
<li>Corrected importing of public keys. Cannot assume that key pairs exist.</li>
<li>Corrected removal of URLs having special characters.</li>
<li>Corrected use of spoton::addFriendsKey().</li>
<li>Custom status messages. A maximum of 64 characters will be imposed.</li>
<li>Denote extreme time deltas in Chat. Currently configured to thirty seconds. Source only.</li>
<li>Digital signatures should vouch for private key information.</li>
<li>Display URL database connection information within the Search panel.</li>
<li>Do not delete URLs from shared.db unless they were properly loaded.<li>
<li>Dual-purpose domain check boxes. Please see URLs.</li>
<li>Encapsulate data into streams and decrease Base-64 conversions. This will result in smaller messages. Previous functionality will be disrupted.</li>
<li>Establish authentication and encryption keys via silent SMP. The 32-byte authentication and 32-byte encryption keys are created from a Whirlpool digest of the SHA-512 digest of the secret.</li>
<li>Guard QList::last().</li>
<li>Guard QList::removeAt().</li>
<li>Notify the user of URL import statistics.</li>
<li>Prompt before accessing a remote URL.</li>
<li>Replace spaces with dashes in StarBeam and e-mail attachment file names.</li>
<li>Simplified copying and exporting of public keys.</li>
<li>Updated NTRU files (05/14/2015).</li>
<li>Verify a StarBeam's provided pulse size against some defined maximum.</li>
</ol>
0.22 (04/29/2015)
<ol>
<li>Added Documentation/Spot-On-Kernel.1.</li>
<li>Added the option 65536 to the File Encryption's Read Size.</li>
<li>Allow modification of StarBeam pulse sizes.</li>
<li>Automatically verify StarBeams. Please see the Options panel.</li>
<li>Corrected QSqlQuery preparation. QSqlQuery::exec() must not be used to prepare SQL statements. (spoton_listener::slotNewConnection(), spoton_misc::savePublishedNeighbo())</li>
<li>Corrected Qt DLLs in the Windows bundle.</li>
<li>Corrected inspection of QSqlQuery::exec() errors in various locations.</li>
<li>Corrected server-side processing of UDP datagrams.</li>
<li>Corrected spoton_misc::prepareUrlDistillersDatabase() and spoton_misc::prepareUrlKeysDatabase() with respect to the ok variables.</li>
<li>Improved error messages in the UI.</li>
<li>Include a file's digest within each StarBeam pulse.</li>
<li>Issue QThread::wait() after QThread::quit().</li>
<li>On Qt 5.x and Windows, assume a fusion style.</li>
<li>QWidget::activateWindow() should only be used on Windows!</li>
<li>Updated SQLite to version 3.8.9, Windows.</li>
</ol>

